/// The base module every dashboard entry `amends`. It carries the scaffold that
/// used to be copy-pasted into each entry — the reflected card registry and the
/// shared theme — so an entry opens with `amends "lib/entry.pkl"` and sets only
/// `card` (plus an optional `title`/`surfaces`, or a `theme` override).
///
/// Slug = the amending entry's filename (ServerApp forces it at decode time).
/// `title` feeds the page `<title>` (Server falls back to the slug when null);
/// `omitNullProperties` drops it from the wire JSON when left unset, so a
/// title-less entry is byte-identical to the pre-base-module scaffold.
///
/// AUTHORING NOTE — the required `card`: because `card` has no default here, an
/// amending entry that forgets to set it fails with
///   "Tried to read property `card` but its value is undefined"
/// whose caret points at THIS module's `card` line (below), NOT at the offending
/// entry (Pkl reports a missing required property at the class/base definition —
/// see the CLAUDE.md Pkl gotchas). If you hit that error, the fix is in YOUR
/// entry: assign `card = new c.Column { ... }` (or another `c.Node`).
module entry

import "components.pkl" as c
import "theme-beer.pkl" as themeMod

/// The component modules whose card classes this dashboard can use. The
/// authoring library is always here; ADD a module to use cards it defines:
///
///   import "@fh-dashboard/components.pkl" as c
///   import "mycards.pkl" as mine
///   componentModules { mine }
///   card = (c.column) { children { mine.gauge(...) } }
///
/// Why this is explicit rather than inferred from your imports: Pkl reflection
/// exposes an import only as a URI string and cannot turn one back into a
/// module, so the library has no way to find your cards unless you name them.
/// Forgetting to register a module you use is a "card not found" from
/// `Dashboard.validate` at build time, not a broken dashboard at runtime.
///
/// Your cards must live in their own module (not inline in this entry): classes
/// in an amending module need `local`, and `local` classes are invisible to
/// reflection, so an inline card class would never register.
hidden componentModules: Listing<Module> = new { c }

/// The reflected card registry (each card class's template + slots), collected
/// from [[componentModules]]. Two modules claiming one card name is an error.
cards = c.cardsOf(componentModules.toList())

/// The shared theme — BeerCSS Material Design 3 (`theme-beer.pkl`; see
/// `theme.pkl` for the contract + roster). Override in an entry that wants a
/// different look (`theme = (import "lib/theme-mine.pkl").theme`, any module
/// exporting a `theme.pkl` Theme) or retune
/// this one by amending (`theme { md3Light { ["primary"] = "#..." } }`).
theme = themeMod.theme

/// The page `<title>`; null (the default, dropped from the wire JSON) means the
/// Server falls back to the dashboard's slug.
title: String? = null

/// Registered popup surfaces (opened by an `openPopup(id)` tap). Inline popups
/// and tab panels ride on their node's `inlineSurfaces` and are hoisted into
/// this registry at build time, so most entries leave this empty.
///
/// The mapping DEFAULT is a [[c.PopupSurface]], so a popup surface amends into
/// existence — no `new`, and the [[c.Popup]] dialog wrap is automatic:
///   surfaces { ["detail"] { body { c.title("...") c.entityCard(e) } } }
/// A non-popup surface is an explicit `["x"] = new c.SurfaceDef { ... }`.
surfaces: Mapping<String, c.SurfaceDef> = new { default = (_) -> new c.PopupSurface {} }

/// The root of the layout tree — the ONE property every entry must set (see the
/// authoring note above about the error location when it is forgotten).
card: c.Node
